author: Emma Elsworthy
title: Coronavirus death toll at Sydney aged-care home reaches five
description: A 96-year-old woman is the fifth resident to die at the Newmarch House after a staff member unintentionally caused a coronavirus outbreak and infected both staff and residents.
content:
Updated 
April 24, 2020 18:31:43
A fifth resident at Newmarch House in Sydney's west who tested positive for COVID-19 has died, aged-care provider Anglicare has confirmed. 
The woman was 96-years-old and had multiple health issues, according to Anglicare.… [+3782 chars]
